> Can you recommend a fairly fast vegetarian dinner recipe that uses bell peppers, celery, and carrots?
**assistant**:
> Absolutely! How about a delicious and colorful stir-fry? Here's a simple recipe for a vegetarian stir-fry that incorporates bell peppers, celery, and carrots:
> 
> Ingredients:
> - 2 bell peppers (any color), thinly sliced
> - 2 stalks of celery, thinly sliced
> - 2 carrots, julienned or thinly sliced
> - 1 onion, thinly sliced
> - 2 cloves of garlic, minced
> - 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil
> - 2 tablespoons of soy sauce (or tamari for a gluten-free option)
> - 1 tablespoon of sesame oil (optional)
> - 1 teaspoon of ginger, grated or minced
> - Salt and pepper to taste
> - Cooked rice or noodles for serving
> 
> Instructions:
> 1. Heat the vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
> 2. Add the sliced onion and minced garlic to the pan and sautÃ© for about 2 minutes until fragrant and slightly softened.
> 3. Add the bell peppers, celery, and carrots to the pan and stir-fry for about 5-7 minutes until the vegetables are crisp-tender, but still vibrant in color.
> 4. In a small bowl, mix together the soy sauce, sesame oil (if using), grated ginger, salt, and pepper.
> 5. Pour the sauce mixture over the vegetables and stir-fry for an additional minute to coat the vegetables evenly.
> 6. Taste and adjust the seasoning if needed.
> 7. Remove from heat and serve the stir-fry over cooked rice or noodles.
> 
> Feel free to customize this recipe by adding other vegetables or ingredients like tofu, mushrooms, or cashews for extra protein and texture. Enjoy your delicious and speedy vegetarian stir-fry!
